SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION—Urging Congress to call a
convention of the states to propose amendments to the
United States Constitution that impose fiscal restraints on
the Federal Government, limit the power and jurisdiction
of the Federal Government and limit the terms of office of
federal officials and members of Congress.
1 WHEREAS, The Framers of our United States Constitution
2 empowered states, Legislatures under Article V, to be guardians of
3 liberty against future abuses of power by the Federal Government
4 by authorizing states to apply for a convention to propose
5 amendments to the Constitution; and
6 WHEREAS, It is the opinion of the Nevada Legislature that the
7 Federal Government has increased the national debt through
8 imprudent spending; and
9 WHEREAS, It is the opinion of the Nevada Legislature that the
10 Federal Government has encroached upon the legitimate roles of the
11 states through the intrusive process of federal mandates, most of
12 which are largely unfunded; and
13 WHEREAS, It is the opinion of the Nevada Legislature that the
14 Federal Government has ceased to operate under a proper
15 interpretation of the United States Constitution; and
16 WHEREAS, It is the solemn duty of the states to protect the
17 liberty of our people, particularly for the generations to come, by
18 proposing amendments to the United States Constitution through a
-
