1 convention of the states under Article V for the purpose of
2 restraining these and related abuses of power by the Federal
3 Government; now, therefore, be it
4 RESOLVED BY THE SENATE AND ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF
5 NEVADA, JOINTLY, That the members of the 83rd Session of the
6 Nevada Legislature hereby urge Congress, under the provisions of
7 Article V of the United States Constitution, to call a convention of
8 the states to propose amendments to the United States Constitution
9 that impose fiscal restraints on the Federal Government, limit the
10 power and jurisdiction of the Federal Government and limit the
11 terms of office for federal officials and members of Congress; and
12 be it further
13 RESOLVED, That this application constitutes a continuing
14 application in accordance with Article V of the United States
15 Constitution until the legislatures of at least two-thirds of the several
16 states have made applications on the same subject; and be it further
17 RESOLVED, That the Secretary of the Senate prepare and
18 transmit a copy of this resolution to the Vice President of the United
19 States as presiding officer of the United States Senate, the Speaker
20 of the House of Representatives, each member of the Nevada
21 Congressional Delegation and to the presiding officers of each of
22 the legislative houses in the several states, requesting their
23 cooperation; and be it further
24 RESOLVED, That this resolution becomes effective upon
25 passage.
